    "actions": [
      {
        "startDie": 1,
        "endDie": 2,
        "name": "Cursed Slash (Physical)",
        "description": "<div><p>The Skeletal Horror swings its weapon with an eerie precision, dealing D6 Slashing damage.</p></div>"
      },
      {
        "startDie": 3,
        "endDie": 4,
        "name": "Ethereal Grasp (Magical)",
        "description": "<div><p>The Skeletal Horror reaches out with its hand, attempting to touch the essence of a target's life force. The target must make an Endurance check. On a failed check, they take D6 Necrotic damage, and the Skeletal Horror regains Health equal to half the damage dealt. On a successful roll, the target takes half damage, and the Skeletal Horror doesn't regain Health.</p></div>"
      },
      {
        "startDie": 5,
        "endDie": 5,
        "name": "Haunting Wail (Magical)",
        "description": "<div><p>The Skeletal Horror lets out a haunting wail that reverberates through the air. All creatures must make a successful Resolve check to avoid becoming Stunned (1).</p></div>"
      },
      {
        "startDie": 6,
        "endDie": 6,
        "name": "Vengeful Onslaught (Physical)",
        "description": "<div><p>The Skeletal Horror charges forward with relentless determination, targeting one creature. It makes a melee attack against the target, dealing D4 Piercing damage on a hit. If the attack hits, the Skeletal Horror immediately uses its Ethereal Grasp ability as a Free Action.</p></div>"
      }
    ],
    "description": "<div><p>The remnants of fallen warriors cursed to wander eternally, these skeletal monsters are shrouded in the tattered remnants of their once-proud armor, their bones blackened and charred by the fires of the afterlife. They wield spectral weapons with an unnatural dexterity, instilling dread in the hearts of any who dare cross their path. Skeletal Horrors mercilessly hunt those who trespass upon their cursed domain with relentless dedication, stopping at nothing to ensure all living creatures are dead.</p></div>",
